Fix BE NOC backend validator to generate with whatever supporting files are
provided. Remove hard-block behavior. Match warning-first pattern from RS
and DEG-EG workflows.

Current issue:
Validator hard-blocks generation with errors like:
- "Main application document was not uploaded"
- "No API could be extracted"
- "Composition table is empty"

There is no "main application document" input for BE NOC. The main document
IS the target output. System must generate from whatever supporting files
user uploads and leave unpopulated sections empty.

Fix in benoc.py backend validator:

1. Remove all hard-block validations for content availability:
   - Missing APIs
   - Empty composition
   - Missing manufacturing process
   - Missing equipment list
   - Missing dissolution data
   - Missing drug substance specifications
   - Missing raw materials
   - Missing manufacturer addresses

2. Hard-block ONLY on true structural failures:
   - No files uploaded at all
   - All uploaded annexures failed extraction completely (every _error=True)

3. Convert content availability checks to WARNINGS (not blockers):
   Each missing section adds a warning to the UI panel:
   - "Section 1 Drug Information partially populated: chemistry lookup used;
     indications and manufacturer address not extracted"
   - "Section 4 Composition table not populated: BMR/MFR not uploaded"
   - "Section 5 Equipment list not populated: BMR/MFR not uploaded"
   - "Section 6 Manufacturing Process narrative not populated: BMR/MFR not uploaded"
   - "Section 7 Manufacturing Process Flow not populated: BMR/MFR not uploaded"
   - "Section 8 Loratadine drug substance specification not populated: Loratadine STP not uploaded"
   - "Section 12 Comparative Dissolution not populated: comparative dissolution report not uploaded"

4. Renderer must handle empty sections gracefully:
   - Section headings still appear
   - Empty body shows "Not provided" placeholder or remains blank
   - No error thrown for missing data
   - Sections with actual data populate normally

5. Add optional metadata form fields (visible in Streamlit) for scientist to
   fill gaps:
   - API details (IUPAC, MW, CAS, indications, manufacturer) — per API
   - Composition rows (optional Excel/CSV upload)
   - Manufacturing process narrative (paste text)
   - Equipment list (optional Excel/CSV upload)
   - Comparative dissolution data (optional Excel upload)
   These are OPTIONAL. If not provided, sections remain empty.

6. Session-state defaults:
   All content categories default to empty lists/None. Nothing throws
   AttributeError on missing keys. Renderer safely checks Array.isArray or
   null before iterating.

7. Warnings displayed in Streamlit UI in a collapsible panel below the
   generation button:
   "Sections partially populated: [list of missing categories]"
   User sees the gap list and can decide to iterate with additional uploads
   or accept partial document.

8. Rendered DOCX must NOT contain "manual review required", "not provided
   pending manual entry", or any warning language in the body. Empty
   sections show a simple placeholder or remain blank.

Acceptance:
Upload only the 12 supporting files (no main application, no BMR, no
Loratadine STP, no comparative dissolution). Generation SUCCEEDS.
